form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Inspection Act of Religious Marriage, N0# 3249 E

full_text: Screened by NARA, 8/7/2023 NO# 3249 E Inscription Act of Religious Marriage Liberty Equality Fraternity Haiti's Republic In the year nineteen sixty-nine, the 166th year of independence, on Friday, July 18; We, Pierre, Augustin, Rene, Salagado the officers of the Civil Registrar of Port-au-Prince, north section; certify that all documents were transmitted to us by the Rev. Attis, the Archbishop of St. Martin, in compliance with Article 6 that was ruled on December 16, 1929 modify by the one on January 26, 1945. We approve, register and certify after all the publicity were strongly done neither opposition has been signified to the Prime Minister; Mister Jeantel Alinska (alias) Jean Lacroix Printer age twenty seven years old. Born at North St. Louis resident of Port-au-Prince. Son of Victoire Lacroix resident of North St. Louis stipulate for him as his personal name and Marie Clenie Gabriel (owner) years of age twenty five. Born at North St. Louis resident of Port-au-Prince daughter of Charles Gabriel resident and Elisabeth Mercedesse, owner resident of North St. Louis stipulate for her as her personal name has been presented on June 17, 1969 at six thirty P.M. at St. Martin's Church for a marriage of contract. At the question are they willing to take each other as spouses, and they each respond separately and affirmatively in the presence of the Religious Prime Minister, to Yvon Duroseaux Lawyer, years of age thirty-two residence Port-au-Prince. 20) Mrs. Carmen Stanisles Seamstress. years of age 45 residence Port-au-Prince they all were also united for the marriage the act directed by the Religious Prime Minister was sign by him(s) Attis Archbishop. in witness whereof have been directed and signed the present act, in compliance to the law. The receipt of the general administration contributions, No# 89354 Series AA Sign: Salagado Coult NOTARY PUBLIC STATE Or FLORID$ MY COMMISSION EXP. JULY 1,1995 BONDED THRU GENERAL INS. UND.
